sentence: Melvin Huston McDaniel (September 6, 1942 â€“ March 31, 2011) was an American country music artist.

Many of his top hits were released in the 1980s, including "Louisiana Saturday Night", "Big Ole Brew", "Stand Up", "Baby's Got Her Blue Jeans On" (which reached number one on the country chart), "I Call It Love", "Stand on It", and a remake of Chuck Berry's "Let It Roll (Let It Rock)".

He was inspired to play music after seeing Elvis Presley on television.
He made his professional debut at age 15 performing in a talent contest at Okmulgee High School.
From there, he had an unsuccessful trip to Nashville, followed by quite a bit of success in Anchorage, Alaska, performing at clubs among the oil fields.
